Standards-Version: 3.8.0

Package: librsplib2
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: RSerPool client/server API library for load distribution and server redundancy
 Reliable Server Pooling (RSerPool) is the IETF's standard (RFC 5351 to RFC 5356) for a
 lightweight server pool and session management framework. It provides highly
 available pool management (that is registration handling and load
 distribution/balancing) by components called Registrar and a
 client-side/server-side API for accessing the service of a pool.
 .
 The API is provided by this package.

Package: librsplib-dev
Section: libdevel
Priority: optional
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, librsplib2
Description: headers of the RSerPool client/server API library rsplib
 Reliable Server Pooling (RSerPool) is the IETF's standard (RFC 5351 to RFC 5356) of a
 lightweight server pool and session management framework. It provides highly
 available pool management (that is registration handling and load
 distribution/balancing) by components called Registrar and a
 client-side/server-side API for accessing the service of a pool.
 .
 This package provides header files for the rsplib library. You need them to
 develop your own RSerPool-based clients and servers.

Package: libcpprspserver2
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Architecture: any
