Package: rsplib-services
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, rsplib-tools
Recommends: rsplib-fgp-cfgfiles
Description: RSerPool example services
 Reliable Server Pooling (RSerPool) is the IETF's standard (RFC 5351 to RFC 5356) for a
 lightweight server pool and session management framework. It provides highly
 available pool management (that is registration handling and load
 distribution/balancing) by components called Registrar and a
 client-side/server-side API for accessing the service of a pool.
 .
 This package provides the rsplib RSerPool example services:
 Echo, Discard, Daytime, CharGen, CalcApp, FractalGenerator, ScriptingService.

Package: rsplib-fgp-cfgfiles
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, rsplib-tools
Description: RSerPool Fractal Generator Service example input files
 Reliable Server Pooling (RSerPool) is the IETF's standard (RFC 5351 to RFC 5356) for a
 lightweight server pool and session management framework. It provides highly
 available pool management (that is registration handling and load
 distribution/balancing) by components called Registrar and a
 client-side/server-side API for accessing the service of a pool.
 .
 This package provides a set of input files for the Fractal Generator service.
